{"article_id":"0omrIAB5ZeiAafLG","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Top takeaways from Doug Jones ' shocking victory over Roy Moore in Alabama","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"CLOSE","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"Democrat Doug Jones won a narrow but stunning victory in Alabama 's Senate race ,","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"defeating Republican Roy Moore in the heavily Republican state .","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"( Dec. 13 ) AP","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"Doug Jones turned the political world on its head Tuesday night ,","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"winning a Senate seat for Democrats in Alabama , a state","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"that had n't elected a Democratic senator in 25 years .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"Here are a few key takeaways from his win over firebrand conservative Roy Moore :","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"Some prominent Republicans ,","depth":12},{"id":10,"text":"including Alabama 's Republican Sen. Richard Shelby ,","depth":12},{"id":11,"text":"suggested","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"it was better to write in somebody else","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"than to vote for Moore ,","depth":12},{"id":14,"text":"who was tainted by allegations","depth":13},{"id":15,"text":"he had romantically pursued and sexually assaulted girls in their teens","depth":14},{"id":16,"text":"when he was in his 30s .","depth":14},{"id":17,"text":"Tuesday night , the Alabama secretary of state tallied 22,780 votes for write-in candidates ,","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"though many of those may ultimately be discarded","depth":12},{"id":19,"text":"because they were not cast far an actual registered candidate .","depth":12},{"id":20,"text":"Jones beat Moore by fewer than 21,000 votes .","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"You do the math .","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"As a point of comparison , in 2016 , Shelby won his re-election 64 % -36 % over a Democratic challenger ,","depth":13},{"id":23,"text":"and there were fewer than 4,000 write-in ballots .","depth":13},{"id":24,"text":"And that was in a presidential year ,","depth":13},{"id":25,"text":"so there were many more voters","depth":15},{"id":26,"text":"participating in the election","depth":15},{"id":27,"text":"( about 2.1 million versus the 1.3 million votes","depth":15},{"id":28,"text":"cast Tuesday night . )","depth":15},{"id":29,"text":"With Jones replacing Republican Sen. Luther Strange in the Senate ,","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"Republicans go from controlling 52 seats to controlling 51 , in a chamber","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"that requires 50 votes","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"to get anything done .","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"Republicans are racing to get a massive tax cut passed before Christmas ,","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"and their majority has already been wobbly ,","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"with several Republican senators hinting","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"they may not vote for the bill .","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"Alabama Secretary of State John Merrill said on CNN Tuesday night","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"he expects to certify the election results the last week of December ; at the latest , the first week of January .","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"So for Democrats and their leader Chuck Schumer of New York , the question now becomes :","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"Can they stall a final vote on the tax bill long enough","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"for Jones to arrive","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"and convert one critical `` yes '' vote into a `` no '' ?","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"Stay tuned .","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"The Democrats owe gratitude to the black voters","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"who showed up","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"and voted for Jones .","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"Dave Wasserman of the nonpartisan Cook Political Report noted on Twitter Tuesday","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"that turnout in heavily black counties was at three-fourths of what it was in the 2016 election .","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"Wasserman also noted","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"that white voters in rural white counties were turning at just over half of the rate","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"they did for the 2016 election .","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"Those numbers are unusual","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"given off-year election turn-out tends to lean Republicans .","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"More :","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"Twitter thanks","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"# BlackWomen","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"for voting for Democrat Doug Jones","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"Amazing :","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"turnout is at 72 % -77 % of '16 presidential race in heavily black counties , but just 55 % -60 % in rural white counties .","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"Black voters","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"punching above their weight tonight","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"& giving Jones a chance .","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"# ALSEN","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"- Dave Wasserman","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"( @ Redistrict )","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"December 13 , 2017","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"And","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"when they showed up","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"they voted for Jones ,","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"the Washington Post ' s exit polls found","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"that 96 % of black voters backed Jones .","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"This is also a victory for Rep. Terri Sewell , the state 's lone Democratic House member ,","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"who organized a caravan of black leaders","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"to come to Alabama","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"to stump for Jones .","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"It evidently paid off .","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"Whether or not you believe the allegations against Moore ,","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"there is no doubt at all","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"they had a dramatic impact on the election .","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"Not a single public poll showed Jones leading Moore prior to the Washington Post 's explosive story","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"quoting Moore 's accusers on the record Nov. 9 .","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"In the days afterward there were more accusers , more stories of bad behavior by Moore and calls from senior Republicans","depth":14},{"id":83,"text":"for Moore to step aside .","depth":14},{"id":84,"text":"The news story fundamentally changed the race .","depth":13},{"id":85,"text":"Late Tuesday , President Trump tweeted a subdued , congratulatory message to Jones ,","depth":14},{"id":86,"text":"making note of the Democrat 's `` hard fought victory . ''","depth":14},{"id":87,"text":"Congratulations to Doug Jones on a hard fought victory .","depth":14},{"id":88,"text":"The write-in votes played a very big factor ,","depth":16},{"id":89,"text":"but a win is a win .","depth":16},{"id":90,"text":"The people of Alabama are great ,","depth":16},{"id":91,"text":"and the Republicans will have another shot at this seat in a very short period of time .","depth":17},{"id":92,"text":"It never ends !","depth":17},{"id":93,"text":"- Donald J. Trump","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"( @ realDonaldTrump )","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"December 13 , 2017","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"When it appeared ,","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"everyone in our newsroom had the same questions :","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"Who wrote that tweet ?","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"It certainly did n't sound like Donald Trump .","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"Was he suddenly turning over a new , more mannerly , leaf ?","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"Wednesday morning the old Donald Trump re-emerged ,","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"claiming","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"he was right all along .","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"Moore had never been his preferred candidate","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"because he was too controversial .","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"`` I was right ! ''","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"The reason","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"I originally endorsed Luther Strange","depth":14},{"id":109,"text":"( and his numbers went up mightily ) ,","depth":14},{"id":110,"text":"is that I said","depth":13},{"id":111,"text":"Roy Moore will not be able to win the General Election .","depth":13},{"id":112,"text":"I was right !","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"Roy worked hard","depth":13},{"id":114,"text":"but the deck was stacked against him !","depth":13},{"id":115,"text":"- Donald J. Trump","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"( @ realDonaldTrump )","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"December 13 , 2017","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":235,"left":0,"right":234,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":234,"left":1,"right":233,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":233,"left":120,"right":232,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":120,"left":119,"right":4,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":119,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":232,"left":158,"right":231,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":158,"left":122,"right":157,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":122,"left":5,"right":121,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":121,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":157,"left":8,"right":156,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":156,"left":145,"right":155,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":145,"left":141,"right":144,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":141,"left":129,"right":140,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":129,"left":124,"right":128,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":124,"left":123,"right":11,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":123,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":12,"right":127,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":127,"left":13,"right":126,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":126,"left":14,"right":125,"relation":"elaboration","nucleari